---
description: "Elysia backend patterns: TypeBox schemas, Eden Treaty, api-types package"
globs: "apps/api/**/*.ts"
alwaysApply: false
---

- Use `Elysia.t` (TypeBox) for all schema validation — never Zod
- Shared schemas live in `packages/api-types` — import from `@nearest-neighbor/api-types`
- Eden Treaty provides end-to-end typed clients: `import type { App }` only, no generated code
- CORS registered before auth handler mount — order matters
- `GET /health` returning `{ status: 'ok' }` required for Fly bluegreen
- Listen on `0.0.0.0:${PORT}` (default 8080)
- Module layout: `apps/api/src/modules/<feature>/{index.ts,service.ts,model.ts}`
- Notifications: write synchronously to DB `notifications` table — no queue or background jobs
- No file storage: ASCII art photos are `text` columns in Postgres
